text: The Cathedral of San Salvador is the cathedral church of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Asidonia-Jerez in Jerez de la Frontera, Andalusia, southern Spain. It was declared Bien de Inter√©s Cultural in 1931. It was elevated to the rank of cathedral in 1980. == Style == Built in the 17th century, it is a mix of Gothic, Baroque and Neoclassicist style. == References == == Other websites == * Official site Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:Jerez de la Frontera Category:17th-century buildings and structures
